radiographic_examinations.findings: Bibasilar atelectasis; no pleural or pericardial effusion; distended gallbladder with surrounding pericholecystic fluid and stranding; central intrahepatic biliary dilatation; the common bile duct measures 7 mm; subcentimeter hypodensity in the cortex of the left kidney likely represents a cyst; no other acute abnormalities noted.
